1
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:07,433
<i>She's so disappointed
in me.</i>

2
00:00:07,433 --> 00:00:10,333
<i>I will never forget
the way she looked at me.</i>

3
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:12,167
<i>Let's just talk
to Chloe again.</i>

4
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:14,500
<i>- Love, go home.
- I will, love.</i>

5
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,267
<i>Argh... Ugh...
F**king untie me!</i>

6
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,667
<i> I don't like your wife.</i>

7
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:20,667
<i>But you know
what I dislike even more?</i>

8
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:23,133
<i> Men like you.</i>

9
00:00:23,133 --> 00:00:24,633
<i>- Argh!
- Argh!</i>

10
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:29,600
<i>Are you going home?
It's almost morning.</i>

11
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,767
<i> Love... Anton's dead...</i>

12
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:34,100
<i>- Put your hands up!
- I didn't do this!</i>

13
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>- Love, what's happening?!
- I didn't do anything wrong!</i>

14
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:45,600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

15
00:01:54,767 --> 00:01:59,867
[PHONE BUZZING]

16
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,167
Hello?

17
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:08,733
What?!

18
00:02:08,733 --> 00:02:13,167
[FOOTSTEPS]

19
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:17,367
Excuse me. Excuse me.
Ryan! Ryan?! Ryan!

20
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,533
[RYAN] Love! Love! Love...

21
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:21,300
- What did they do to you?
- [LOCSIN] Oh, Beth!

22
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,867
W-Why are you full of blood?

23
00:02:22,867 --> 00:02:24,767
- Did they hurt you? Why are--
- [LOCSIN] Beth! Beth.

24
00:02:24,767 --> 00:02:26,567
Why is he handcuffed, Locsin?!

25
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:28,467
What did you do to him?!
What did you do to my husband?!

26
00:02:28,467 --> 00:02:29,933
We didn't hurt him, Beth.

27
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:32,600
But he's a suspect in the death
of Anton Montenegro!

28
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,800
What?! Is this a joke?!

29
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,600
Locsin, you know my husband
could never do that!

30
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:41,400
I'm sorry, but this is my job.
We found him all bloody.

31
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,367
He was right next
to the murder weapon,

32
00:02:42,367 --> 00:02:44,233
and right in front
of the victim's body!

33
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:46,600
Even if it's the corpse
of the most corrupt politician,

34
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,700
he'd never do that!
My husband is not a killer!

35
00:02:50,767 --> 00:02:52,567
Love... It's fine.

36
00:02:52,567 --> 00:02:53,933
- We can fix this.
- What do you mean it's fine?!

37
00:02:53,933 --> 00:02:55,433
Remove his handcuffs!

38
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:56,600
Let's just talk
at the police station.

39
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,300
[BETH] Locsin, you know
my husband could never do this!

40
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:01,767
Get my husband out of there!
This isn't him!

41
00:03:01,767 --> 00:03:04,500
You know he didn't kill Anton!
What's with you?!

42
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,767
- Beth, calm down.
- Calm down?!

43
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:09,800
How, when they're going to
imprison my innocent husband?!

44
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,767
[BETH] Locsin, remove
his handcuffs!

45
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:14,367
Beth... Please.

46
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:17,633
[MAN 1] Her husband's dead.

47
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:20,567
They could make
more sex videos now!

48
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,600
- [MAN 2] Yeah.
- [MAN 3] Look at her.

49
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,300
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

50
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,433
[BETH] Locsin.

51
00:03:25,433 --> 00:03:28,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:30,367
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

53
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:32,333
[ALICE] Beth, let Erica
fix this.

54
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,867
You know she'll help you.

55
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:36,033
[ERICA] Did you read him
his rights?

56
00:03:36,033 --> 00:03:37,367
Yes.

57
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:40,700
Ryan, don't talk
until I'm not there.

58
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,000
I'll follow you to the station.

59
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:46,333
Love...
Everything will be okay.

60
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,533
We'll get through this.

61
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:55,467
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:03:57,467 --> 00:04:00,367
[ENGINE HUMS]

63
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,267
[PHONE RINGING]

64
00:04:05,033 --> 00:04:05,967
Hello?

65
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:08,467
[EDONG] How's your husband?

66
00:04:08,467 --> 00:04:09,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,867
You bastard!

68
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,333
How does it feel, Beth...

69
00:04:15,967 --> 00:04:19,333
to be accused of a crime...

70
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:22,333
...you didn't do?

71
00:04:23,033 --> 00:04:25,700
You did this, didn't you?!
You did this!

72
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,367
You did all of this,
didn't you?!

73
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,567
Why are you doing this?!

74
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:35,067
[EDONG LAUGHING]

75
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:38,733
Wow, ma'am is
acting innocent...

76
00:04:39,767 --> 00:04:41,533
...and pretending to be stupid.

77
00:04:41,533 --> 00:04:46,833
[EDONG LAUGHING]

78
00:04:49,933 --> 00:04:54,433
I want to make you feel
what you made me feel, Beth.

79
00:04:54,433 --> 00:04:56,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:58,900
You're a liar...

81
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,067
Beth.

82
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:04,800
<i>You want to imprison
and punish others</i>

83
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,833
like what you did to me.

84
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:11,433
You want to destroy lives...

85
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:14,633
and separate them
from their families...

86
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:17,767
...like what you did
to me and my brother.

87
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:23,033
<i>Don't you teach this
to your students, Beth?</i>

88
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:27,933
That what you reap, Beth...

89
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,000
...is what you sow.

90
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:35,467
<i> Now...</i>

91
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:38,467
<i> The man you love...</i>

92
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:42,067
[EDONG CHUCKLING]

93
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,700
...will also suffer.

94
00:05:45,667 --> 00:05:49,700
He'll be hurt the same way
you made me feel.

95
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:53,533
<i>There's nothing
you can do, Beth.</i>

96
00:05:55,667 --> 00:05:58,967
<i>There's nothing
you can do, but watch.</i>

97
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,033
<i> You know it yourself, Beth...</i>

98
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,633
that it is all...

99
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:10,467
It is all your fault!

100
00:06:10,467 --> 00:06:13,433
You d**n b**tard! D**n you!

101
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:16,467
Why are you doing this,
you b**tard?! You demon!

102
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:18,600
You're a demon!

103
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,333
[BETH SOBBING]

104
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,633
[BETH] Why are you doing this?!

105
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:25,967
[BETH SOBBING]

106
00:06:25,967 --> 00:06:28,367
Why not me?! Huh?!

107
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,933
[BETH SOBBING]

108
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,600
[ERICA]<i> You've already taken
</i> a lot from them!

109
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,433
Why don't you take revenge
on me?!

110
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:36,833
[EDONG]<i> But I've been doing
</i> that to you

111
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,000
<i> for a long time now...</i>

112
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:39,900
<i> Attorney.</i>

113
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:45,800
You want to save people, right?

114
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,633
But you didn't save anyone.

115
00:06:50,967 --> 00:06:52,100
Not a single one...

116
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:55,833
...from me.

117
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:58,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:58,033 --> 00:07:02,800
<i> You couldn't do anything,
Attorney...</i> [CHUCKLES]

119
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,967
<i> But watch them cry...</i>

120
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:10,033
<i>...and get angry,
while they lose everything.</i>

121
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:15,100
You're useless, Attorney.

122
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,833
<i> You are worthless.</i>

123
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,067
[ANNETTE] Die!

124
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:24,867
[EDONG]<i> You're not
</i> a savior, Attorney.

125
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:27,100
[ANNETTE]<i> You shouldn't have
</i> been born!

126
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:28,700
<i> You shouldn't be alive!</i>

127
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:31,433
<i>You'll just become
like your father.</i>

128
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:33,067
<i> I should have killed you!</i>

129
00:07:33,067 --> 00:07:35,500
<i> D**n you! Die!</i>

130
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,667
[EDONG] You know what you are?

131
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,867
You are a fake hero.

132
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:44,900
Fake...

133
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,533
...hero.

134
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:49,167
[EDONG CHUCKLES]

135
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:54,667
<i>Just like the pity
you gave me before.</i>

136
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:59,900
You didn't do anything
to help me, Attorney.

137
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:03,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,400
<i>I've been taking something
from you for a long time now.</i>

139
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:12,467
<i>I'm slowly destroying
everything</i>

140
00:08:12,467 --> 00:08:14,867
<i> you think you stand for.</i>

141
00:08:17,067 --> 00:08:18,867
Don't you feel it?

142
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,600
Attorney?

143
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:24,467
[EDONG INHALES]

144
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:27,467
I am destroying you.

145
00:08:27,467 --> 00:08:34,233
[EDONG CHUCKLING]

146
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:38,100
When are you going to stop?!

147
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:41,567
What else is there, Edong?!
What more do you want,

148
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:43,067
so we can end this?!

149
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:46,633
I'm not going to stop
until I've ruined everything

150
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:48,567
you want to save.

151
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:51,933
<i> Everything will be ruined,</i>

152
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:54,733
<i>nothing will be left.
Not even one.</i>

153
00:08:55,800 --> 00:09:00,567
You all built your lives
because of a lie.

154
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:05,933
You ruined my life
because of a lie.

155
00:09:07,133 --> 00:09:08,767
What did you think, Attorney?

156
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:14,233
That your lies
could protect you forever?

157
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,100
<i> I'll get my revenge.</i>

158
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:20,233
<i> And you will pay.</i>

159
00:09:21,133 --> 00:09:23,933
Accept it now, Attorney.

160
00:09:25,867 --> 00:09:28,133
You won't save anyone.

161
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:35,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

162
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,833
- You were cheating on me?!
- Ouch, ouch.

163
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:47,967
- What?! How dare you!
- [MAN] That wasn't me!

164
00:09:47,967 --> 00:09:50,133
[WOMAN] I don't care!
Bebang reported you!

165
00:09:50,133 --> 00:09:52,667
- [MAN] She's just accusing me.
- [WOMAN] Accusing you?!

166
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:55,767
She saw your hand
on Marie's thigh!

167
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:58,933
- How dare you...
- I'm not cheating on you.

168
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:03,633
Edong called you?

169
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:07,167
[BETH] Edong talked to me,
but he also talked to Erica.

170
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:11,667
It's like he already confessed
to killing Anton, right?

171
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:14,200
[BETH] He wants to get back
at us! You know that!

172
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,900
You even gave us
a protection detail, remember?

173
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:20,767
It's unfortunate the shop
isn't part of our surveillance.

174
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:22,867
I only remembered
when we were on our way.

175
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:25,700
If you were monitoring it,
this wouldn't have happened!

176
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,767
[ERICA] Wait, you said
a tipster messaged you.

177
00:10:27,767 --> 00:10:30,867
- Do you know who that was?
- It was an anonymous tip.

178
00:10:30,867 --> 00:10:32,867
It only said there was
a murder in Ryan's shop.

179
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,933
That was also Edong.

180
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:38,767
If they have the same number,
we have circumstantial proof

181
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,733
that can help
our frame of theory.

182
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:48,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:10:48,267 --> 00:10:50,700
It's the same!
Did you record the call?

184
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,067
No! But shouldn't
this be enough evidence?

185
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:55,033
Ryan should be acquitted!

186
00:10:55,033 --> 00:10:57,200
[LOCSIN] It still needs to go
through the proper process.

187
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,733
When he arrived,
just after 6AM,

188
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:03,267
that began his 36 hours
under inquest detention.

189
00:11:03,267 --> 00:11:06,100
So, before
it turns 6PM tomorrow,

190
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,767
we have to take him
to the prosecution,

191
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,067
along with the police report

192
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:11,300
and possible evidence
against him.

193
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:12,833
Only then will
the prosecutor decide

194
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:14,133
if he should be charged
or not.

195
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:15,800
[BETH] Is it possible
for him to be sued?

196
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,633
Huh? Is it possible?
What if...

197
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:19,833
- Erica, what if...
- It'll be difficult for them.

198
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:22,000
The prosecution now looks
for heavy evidence,

199
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,833
not just probable cause.

200
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,933
They'll only take it to court
if they think

201
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:28,300
there's a realistic chance
for Ryan to be found guilty.

202
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:32,100
If the evidence is weak, they
will release Ryan right away.

203
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,367
Does that mean he'll stay here,
while we wait for the decision?

204
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:38,100
Yes. And while we're moving,

205
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:41,333
only medico-legal can prove if
Ryan's injuries are consistent

206
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,833
with the fact
that he was unconscious

207
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,433
before the police arrived.

208
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:45,967
If that's put in the report,

209
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:48,100
we can question
the validity of the arrest.

210
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:51,100
Is there still no medico-legal
officer available?

211
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:54,967
Negative. They were all
deployed in Liwayway

212
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:56,267
because of a group ambush.

213
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,000
But we're reaching out
to other medico-legal officers

214
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,867
in nearby towns.

215
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:04,467
I hope someone's available.

216
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:06,300
We'll have them picked up
right away.

217
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,367
Alice and Mel are also
in the hospital.

218
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:10,767
They're talking
to Mel's family friends.

219
00:12:10,767 --> 00:12:13,967
They're checking if
there are medico-legal doctors

220
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:15,967
available in nearby towns.

221
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,867
I hope
they have some good news.

222
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:19,733
The injury on the back
of Ryan's head,

223
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:23,000
shouldn't that be evidence?
Evidence that he was set up!

224
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:25,900
[ERICA] That's right, Beth.
But that all depends

225
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,800
on the findings
of medico-legal.

226
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:28,900
But don't worry.

227
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:31,033
Marco already began
an independent investigation.

228
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,000
Lucas is helping, too.

229
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:37,067
Everything they can get,
along with our sworn statements

230
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:39,000
about Edong's call...

231
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,333
I'll use those in the inquest

232
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:42,133
to weaken their case
against Ryan.

233
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:46,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:49,200
- Love!
- Beth. You can't touch him.

235
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:53,000
A medico-legal officer has
to check him first.

236
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,467
The evidence might be ruined.

237
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:59,233
Crime Ops cleaned only
a few parts of his body...

238
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,767
...to prevent him
from getting infected.

239
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:03,900
But everything was documented
before that.

240
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,967
You explain this
to Chloe, okay?

241
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:12,767
Tell her,
her father's not a murderer.

242
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:13,733
What's with you?

243
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:15,833
Even if they show
millions of evidence,

244
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,833
she'd never believe
that you could kill someone.

245
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,367
Love, we're going
to fix this, okay?

246
00:13:20,367 --> 00:13:22,167
We'll get you out of here,
I promise.

247
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:24,267
